text: Jillian Williams (born March 5, 1997) is an American sitting volleyball player. She competed at the 2018 World ParaVolley World Championships, and 2020 Summer Paralympics. She graduated from Texas Lutheran University, and University of Central Oklahoma. == References == == Other websites == * Jillian Williams, a cancer survivor and world champion volleyball player, opens up about her amputation (today.com) April 19, 2019 Category:1997 births Category:American sitting volleyball players Category:Living people
